er, and art-making. Sounds: The Ambient Humanities significantly engages, provokes, and contributes to the dynamic field and inquiry of sound studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSound (Philosophy) 0aSound (Philosophy). 0aSoundsxPolitical aspects. 0aSoundsxPsychological aspects. 0aSoundsxSocial aspects. 0aSoundsxSociological aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aart making.  aaudit sound.  acodified signals.  acultural studies.  aculturally resonant sound.  adialogue.  aecho.  aepistemology.  afilm studies.  agasp.  ahumanistic approach.  aindustrial sounds.  ainterdisciplinary.  aliterary studies.  amedia studies.  amemory.  amusic studies.  amusic.  aparadigms of thought.  apolitical intent.  apolitical significance.  aprivacy.  aresonance.  aresponse.  asilence.  asocial intent.  asocial order.  asound studies.  asound.  aspeech.  astudy of sounds.  atypes of sounds.  awhistle.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028462340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096040440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520960404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520960404/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY